{
  "message": "fuzz: add termwiz::input::InputParser target for raw keystroke bytes (ft-t4n0z)\n\nInputParser::parse accepts untrusted &[u8] from stdin (arrow keys,\nfunction keys, mouse events, CSI u, bracketed paste, OSC responses).\nNo existing target covered it \u2014 termwiz_csi_parser fuzzes the output\nescape-parser crate, and escape_parser_raw covers terminal output, not\nkeyboard input.\n\nHarness exercises both maybe_more={false,true} paths and follows the\nmaybe_more=true path with parse(b\"\", false) to flush any deferred\npartial sequence, matching the intended client protocol.\n\nCorpus: 25 seeds drawn from termwiz/src/input.rs test fixtures covering\nCSI cursor/function/u keys, SS3, SGR and legacy mouse reports, bracketed\npaste markers, OSC 52 clipboard responses, and control characters.\n\nVerified: cargo fuzz build termwiz_input_parser (release, debug=1).\n\nCo-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.7 (1M context) <noreply@anthropic.com>",
  "files": [
    {
      "sha": "1a4dbb090c69911733c012490bc0953d5a25860e",
